OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F425A1775049067
OL,3,CNewcastle United sells St James' Park
OL,4,Cto club owners
OL,6,FNewcastle made a profit after tax of
OL,7,F#34.7m, driven in part by a 44 per
OL,8,Fcent increase in commercial revenue as
OL,9,Fturnover rose by #15m to a record
OL,10,F#335.3m - around half that of the
OL,11,Flikes of Liverpool, Manchester City,
OL,12,FManchester United and Arsenal.
OL,14,FThe group strategic report revealed
OL,15,Fthe club has effectively sold St
OL,16,FJames' Park to its immediate parent
OL,17,Fcompany PZ Newco Limited for #172.1m
OL,18,Fand leased it back, meaning the
OL,19,Ffinancial burden of any future stadium
OL,20,Fdevelopment would not fall on the club
OL,21,Fitself.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/4
